WEBVTT

00:01.936 --> 00:03.369
BRUNI:
Behind every plantation,

00:03.371 --> 00:04.670
there is this
dark history.

00:04.672 --> 00:07.106
- Nice?
- No.

00:07.108 --> 00:08.207
MICHELLE: Not joking.

00:08.209 --> 00:10.175
I am really terrified
of this place.

00:10.177 --> 00:12.644
- That was a "Yeah."
- What?!

00:12.646 --> 00:15.147
And right after the war,
in 1868, he did commit suicide.

00:17.318 --> 00:19.818
Ho ho ho ho ho.

00:22.056 --> 00:24.356
Something just
touched that bear.

00:24.358 --> 00:28.260
What happened to you
after the Civil War?

00:28.262 --> 00:30.562
Suicide.

00:32.633 --> 00:34.466
[ Crows cawing ]

00:34.468 --> 00:38.203
BRUNI: When the dead are
forgotten, they become restless.

00:38.205 --> 00:40.406
Oh, my God!
You just touched me.
What? I did not touch you.

00:40.408 --> 00:42.074
I'm Amy Bruni.

00:42.076 --> 00:45.244
A haunting encounter
redefined my life.

00:45.246 --> 00:48.680
I live with that experience
and seek answers to the unknown.

00:48.682 --> 00:50.749
It says, "I am."

00:50.751 --> 00:52.484
I'm Adam Berry.

00:52.486 --> 00:55.654
At Gettysburg, the shadows
and screams of dead soldiers

00:55.656 --> 00:57.923
turned me
into a supernatural believer.

00:57.925 --> 00:59.458
Oh, my God.

00:59.460 --> 01:02.728
Together, our investigations
bring peace to the living...

01:02.730 --> 01:04.863
You can't scare us,
you can't deter us.

01:04.864 --> 01:06.765
...by giving a voice
to the dead.

01:06.767 --> 01:08.667
I'm going to ask you
one more time.

01:08.669 --> 01:10.169
What is your name?

01:10.171 --> 01:13.105
Because we believe the dead
and the living are all...

01:13.107 --> 01:14.940
kindred spirits.
Kindred spirits.

01:14.942 --> 01:19.511
♪♪

01:19.513 --> 01:23.148
We're on our way to
Belle Grove Plantation.

01:23.150 --> 01:26.385
BRUNI: Belle Grove Plantation

01:26.387 --> 01:30.289
was built
between 1794 and 1797.

01:30.291 --> 01:32.291
It is the birthplace
of the fourth President

01:32.293 --> 01:35.094
of the United States,
James Madison,

01:35.096 --> 01:37.963
and played a crucial role
in the Civil War.

01:37.965 --> 01:39.965
Michelle, who we're meeting
with tonight,

01:39.967 --> 01:42.301
lives at the plantation
with her husband.

01:42.303 --> 01:44.703
They turned Belle Grove
into a bed-and-breakfast.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.004
Michelle has called us

01:46.006 --> 01:47.940
because even though
she believes

01:47.942 --> 01:50.309
Belle Grove is haunted,
very recently,

01:50.311 --> 01:51.677
she feels
as though the activity

01:51.679 --> 01:56.381
has just gotten darker
and darker,

01:56.383 --> 01:59.785
especially around
the caretaker's cottage.

01:59.787 --> 02:01.120
Whatever is out there

02:01.122 --> 02:03.222
is threatening her
and her guests.

02:03.224 --> 02:05.190
This activity has gotten
to a point

02:05.192 --> 02:07.659
that she wants
to burn it down.

02:09.395 --> 02:11.663
You have to remember not only
is this their business,

02:11.665 --> 02:13.232
but this is
where they live.

02:13.234 --> 02:15.634
So it just makes the stakes
even higher for them

02:15.636 --> 02:18.403
because not only are
they concerned for themselves,

02:18.405 --> 02:20.672
but for their
potential guests.

02:20.674 --> 02:22.374
She just wants to make
sure everyone is safe.

02:22.376 --> 02:24.076
Absolutely.

02:24.078 --> 02:27.512
♪♪

02:27.514 --> 02:28.680
Plantations are beautiful.

02:28.682 --> 02:29.915
I mean, look at this.
- Yeah.

02:29.917 --> 02:32.317
But behind
every plantation,

02:32.319 --> 02:35.721
there is this dark history
that could cause a haunting,

02:35.723 --> 02:39.358
and I'm just wondering
what here has changed.

02:39.360 --> 02:41.193
Well, hopefully
she's ready for us

02:41.195 --> 02:42.728
'cause
we're ready for her.

02:42.730 --> 02:45.864
Yeah, so, let's go in and see
what she has to say here.

02:45.866 --> 02:50.669
♪♪

02:50.671 --> 02:53.138
[ Knock on door ]

02:53.140 --> 02:54.573
- Hey. How are you?
- Hi.

02:54.575 --> 02:56.275
Good.
Good to see you.

02:56.277 --> 02:59.144
♪♪

02:59.146 --> 03:01.180
MICHELLE: There's a lot
that has happened.

03:01.182 --> 03:03.515
BRUNI: Really? Just activity's
been getting crazier?

03:03.517 --> 03:04.716
A lot.
Crazy.

03:04.718 --> 03:05.918
- Okay.
- Okay.

03:05.920 --> 03:07.319
Well, then, let's go.
Where should we go?

03:07.321 --> 03:08.854
We're gonna go upstairs
to the Madison Room

03:08.856 --> 03:10.656
and the Turner Room.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.357
The Turner Room
is actually one

03:12.359 --> 03:15.427
of the most haunted locations
in the house,

03:15.429 --> 03:17.930
but I will tell you
that the Madison Room

03:17.932 --> 03:20.566
has been
very active lately.

03:22.436 --> 03:25.304
And we've actually had
quite a lot of activity

03:25.306 --> 03:26.805
lately in
this particular room.

03:26.807 --> 03:30.175
We also have a little
boy ghost named Jacob.

03:30.177 --> 03:31.076
- Hmm.
- Okay.

03:31.078 --> 03:32.878
He's very mischievous.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.580
He likes to play
upstairs.

03:34.582 --> 03:36.582
We'll hear balls
bouncing in the hallway.

03:36.584 --> 03:38.083
Right in
between rooms, right?

03:38.085 --> 03:40.252
- Right.
- What else happens in here?

03:40.254 --> 03:44.823
One that we're getting a lot of
is the Lady in White.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.925
She's been seen
several times in here.

03:46.927 --> 03:49.294
Do you have any idea
who that Lady in White might be?

03:49.296 --> 03:51.863
We think she may be
Carrie Turner.

03:51.865 --> 03:53.932
This house used to belong
to the Turner family

03:53.934 --> 03:56.168
from 1839 to 1894.

03:56.170 --> 03:58.637
We actually have a photograph
of the Lady in White

03:58.639 --> 04:01.240
sitting on this side
of the bed over here.

04:01.242 --> 04:02.274
Hmm.

04:02.276 --> 04:04.276
Would this have
been her room?

04:04.278 --> 04:05.810
- Possibly.
- Okay.

04:05.812 --> 04:08.080
That, or it would have been
her room across the hall.

04:08.082 --> 04:09.781
All right.

04:09.783 --> 04:14.453
♪♪

04:14.455 --> 04:17.189
This is
the Turner Room.

04:17.190 --> 04:18.991
Over in the window here,

04:18.993 --> 04:21.326
there's actually
an etching.

04:23.097 --> 04:25.230
This says, "Carrie Turner,

04:25.232 --> 04:28.133
M. Van Den Burgh,
May 18th, 1869."

04:28.135 --> 04:29.501
Wow!

04:29.503 --> 04:31.737
So, Carrie Turner, who we think
is the Lady in White,

04:31.739 --> 04:33.105
actually wrote her name
in the window.

04:33.107 --> 04:34.306
So that kind of
gives me an idea

04:34.308 --> 04:36.575
that she might be attached
to the house.

04:36.577 --> 04:39.077
♪♪

04:39.079 --> 04:41.179
This room, we do get
a lot of activity.

04:41.181 --> 04:43.048
I have heard things.

04:43.050 --> 04:46.184
I have
heard conversations.

04:46.186 --> 04:47.352
It's just very active.

04:47.354 --> 04:49.454
And it's not
just at nighttime.

04:49.456 --> 04:51.056
It's all the time.

04:51.058 --> 04:52.224
Wow.

04:52.226 --> 04:53.792
And so that's new.

04:53.794 --> 04:55.427
It has not always been
that active.

04:55.429 --> 04:57.696
It's intensified probably
over the last two years.

04:57.698 --> 04:58.897
- Okay.
- Okay.

04:58.899 --> 05:01.566
What do you think was
the catalyst for that?

05:01.568 --> 05:02.868
We've got a lot
more people coming,

05:02.870 --> 05:07.039
and, you know, change
seems to stir things up.

05:07.041 --> 05:08.307
Okay.

05:08.309 --> 05:10.375
What should we
look at next?

05:10.377 --> 05:12.077
Maybe we'll head
to the library.

05:12.079 --> 05:18.150
♪♪

05:18.152 --> 05:19.885
So, this is our library.

05:19.887 --> 05:21.653
Oh, okay.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.388
These are artifacts
that we have found

05:23.390 --> 05:24.356
here on the property.

05:24.358 --> 05:25.857
We find things
all the time,

05:25.859 --> 05:30.028
and we have things
from almost every time period.

05:30.030 --> 05:33.365
This is actually a piece
that we found.

05:33.367 --> 05:35.434
This is a nail
that's been curled.

05:35.436 --> 05:37.035
- That's really cool.
- Okay.

05:37.037 --> 05:39.871
And what it is,
is it's a talisman.

05:39.873 --> 05:42.240
And so the slaves that
came over from Africa,

05:42.242 --> 05:44.509
they would bring
their religion with them.

05:44.511 --> 05:46.745
Not Voodoo, but Hoodoo.
- Hmm.

05:46.747 --> 05:49.181
And so this is a form
of Hoodoo.

05:49.183 --> 05:52.050
They would create things
by curling the iron,

05:52.052 --> 05:53.919
and it would
become a talisman

05:53.921 --> 05:55.454
to keep evil spirits away.

05:56.890 --> 05:58.623
You guys strongly believe

05:58.625 --> 06:01.827
that that came from
the slaves that were here.

06:01.829 --> 06:03.995
I actually had an archeologist
look at it,

06:03.997 --> 06:06.031
and they helped me
by dating things.

06:06.033 --> 06:08.367
So, do you think that
they had a reason

06:08.369 --> 06:10.802
to believe they needed
to keep something evil out,

06:10.804 --> 06:12.838
or is this just something
they did all the time?

06:12.840 --> 06:14.406
I don't know.

06:14.408 --> 06:15.841
That's interesting.

06:15.843 --> 06:17.609
I've never seen
that before.

06:17.611 --> 06:19.578
Mnh-mnh. Where was this
specifically found?

06:19.580 --> 06:21.279
Over by
the caretaker's house,

06:21.281 --> 06:23.648
where the actual
slave quarters was.

06:25.285 --> 06:26.985
Where to next?

06:26.987 --> 06:29.988
♪♪

06:29.990 --> 06:31.723
So, we're gonna
go down here.

06:31.725 --> 06:34.359
♪♪

06:34.361 --> 06:35.827
This is
our Winter Kitchen,

06:35.829 --> 06:38.363
and slaves would have
brought the food over.

06:38.365 --> 06:40.665
They would heat it up here
to take up to the family.

06:40.667 --> 06:44.369
We have a lot of activity
down here.

06:44.371 --> 06:45.637
And what happens
down here?

06:45.639 --> 06:47.873
I was actually loading stuff
in the dryer,

06:47.875 --> 06:49.708
and all of a sudden, I heard
someone standing behind me

06:49.710 --> 06:52.511
with a very deep, gruff voice,
and he muttered something.

06:52.513 --> 06:54.079
Couldn't hear what
he was saying.

06:54.081 --> 06:55.547
Wow.

06:55.549 --> 06:56.681
Where do you feel, like,

06:56.683 --> 06:58.417
most uncomfortable
on the property?

06:58.419 --> 07:00.485
There's one place
that I will not go

07:00.487 --> 07:03.455
because I have very
bad feelings around it.

07:03.457 --> 07:06.892
It's the caretaker's
house.

07:06.894 --> 07:08.760
The person
that's in the house

07:08.762 --> 07:10.328
that has claimed
that space

07:10.330 --> 07:11.930
can be threatening
at times.

07:11.932 --> 07:14.232
I personally do not do
anything around it.

07:14.234 --> 07:16.701
I try to stay away from it.
- Do you go in it?

07:16.703 --> 07:18.737
No.
The one time I walked in,

07:18.739 --> 07:20.205
I turned around
and walked right back out.

07:20.207 --> 07:21.840
And I won't go back in.
- Okay.

07:21.842 --> 07:24.443
So, do you want to show us
the caretaker's house?

07:24.445 --> 07:27.045
Yes, but I am not
going inside.

07:27.047 --> 07:36.087
♪♪

07:36.089 --> 07:38.757
Well, I can see why
you think it's creepy.

07:38.759 --> 07:40.091
I mean...

07:40.093 --> 07:43.328
I think it was built sometime
between 1930 and 1940.

07:43.330 --> 07:45.163
What's your plan
for this building, eventually?

07:45.165 --> 07:47.132
We need to burn
the house down.

07:47.134 --> 07:48.433
- Really? Get rid of it.
- Yeah.

07:48.435 --> 07:49.935
So you feel that strongly
about it.

07:49.937 --> 07:52.337
Yeah.

07:52.339 --> 07:53.405
I'm not joking.

07:53.407 --> 07:55.040
I am really terrified
of this place.

07:55.042 --> 07:56.975
I do not like going inside
at all.

07:56.977 --> 07:58.343
Okay.

07:58.345 --> 07:59.544
When was the last time
someone lived in this house?

07:59.546 --> 08:00.779
About four years ago.

08:00.781 --> 08:03.181
And how did
they feel about it?

08:03.183 --> 08:05.183
I know
they saw stuff here.

08:05.185 --> 08:07.352
Has anything else
happened?

08:07.354 --> 08:08.887
I've had people
that have gone inside,

08:08.889 --> 08:11.890
and it said some really,
very nasty things.

08:11.892 --> 08:13.825
It talks
about hurting people.

08:13.827 --> 08:17.028
It talks about,
"Get out," "Run,"

08:17.030 --> 08:20.165
"Push," "Death,"
"Hanging."

08:20.167 --> 08:22.000
Anything to get people
out of the house.

08:24.204 --> 08:27.305
Do you have any idea who or what
could be causing the activity?

08:27.307 --> 08:29.774
We think he may be
an old overseer.

08:29.776 --> 08:31.209
Hmm.

08:31.211 --> 08:34.044
This 1856 map
that we have shows

08:34.047 --> 08:35.981
that this is where
the slave quarters started,

08:35.982 --> 08:38.616
and it ran all the way
down this way.

08:38.619 --> 08:39.951
Oh!

08:39.953 --> 08:41.352
What do you think initiated
the shift here,

08:41.355 --> 08:43.922
where this became
kind of a negative space?

08:43.924 --> 08:45.724
Change seems
to stir things up

08:45.726 --> 08:48.293
because there's a lot
of construction stuff around.

08:48.295 --> 08:52.197
Is there anything
that we could do or find out

08:52.199 --> 08:55.033
that would help you
go into this building?

08:55.035 --> 08:56.835
I would have to know
that it's completely clean.

08:56.837 --> 08:58.136
That,
or who it is, yes.

08:58.138 --> 08:59.871
Okay.

09:02.009 --> 09:04.342
Honestly, it's just
very scary for me.

09:04.344 --> 09:05.777
I know. I see it.
I see it in you.

09:05.779 --> 09:06.778
- Yeah.
- I mean, I see it.

09:06.780 --> 09:07.846
I can tell.
- Yeah.

09:07.848 --> 09:08.947
What if we fix
whatever was here?

09:08.949 --> 09:10.048
Would you go in it?

09:10.050 --> 09:11.983
- I would try.
- Yeah.

09:11.985 --> 09:13.952
This is as close
as I really want to get.

09:13.954 --> 09:16.421
Okay, well, you don't
have to go any further.

09:16.423 --> 09:18.189
I know you're planning
to go out of town.

09:18.191 --> 09:19.624
Yes.

09:19.626 --> 09:21.159
If we have any questions,
we'll call you up.

09:21.161 --> 09:22.394
Okay, yeah.

09:22.396 --> 09:23.595
Well, let's go get
our gear together.

09:23.597 --> 09:25.063
- Yeah.
- All right.

09:25.065 --> 09:27.766
BRUNI: Michelle is convinced
that the caretaker's cottage

09:27.768 --> 09:29.868
is the center
of the dark activity,

09:29.870 --> 09:33.572
