He was essentially
a slave driver.

28:09.188 --> 28:10.621
Mm-hmm.

28:10.623 --> 28:12.222
One can imagine there's still
a range of violence

28:12.224 --> 28:14.124
one would use there.

28:14.126 --> 28:15.759
All of those
are open questions.

28:15.761 --> 28:17.861
And it's certainly possible here
there's more to know.

28:17.863 --> 28:19.329
- Yeah.
- Sure.

28:19.331 --> 28:21.598
BERRY: We now know
Lee killed himself.

28:21.600 --> 28:24.268
So he was obviously
a very troubled man.

28:24.270 --> 28:26.236
If he is in the cottage,
we need to learn more

28:26.238 --> 28:29.106
about what kind of person
we're dealing with.

28:29.108 --> 28:30.808
We called in Rita Wagstaff,

28:30.810 --> 28:32.910
a professor of
African American Studies.

28:32.912 --> 28:36.847
She can tell us more about
his role as an overseer.

28:36.849 --> 28:37.981
BRUNI:
I mean, being here now,

28:37.983 --> 28:39.283
it looks so different
from how it did.

28:39.285 --> 28:41.418
And so we're trying
to just understand

28:41.420 --> 28:42.619
what life was like.

28:42.621 --> 28:44.455
Where we're standing, like,
slave quarters

28:44.457 --> 28:47.458
started about here
and extended this way.

28:47.460 --> 28:50.094
And at one point, I think
they had 192 slaves...

28:50.096 --> 28:51.195
Wow!

28:51.197 --> 28:53.130
...at one point
on this property,

28:53.132 --> 28:54.164
the Turner family.

28:54.166 --> 28:58.936
There was an overseer,
who I guess --

28:58.938 --> 29:00.404
did he manage?

29:00.406 --> 29:01.805
What was his job?

29:01.807 --> 29:03.640
The overseer was the white man
on the plantation

29:03.642 --> 29:05.709
who was in charge
of working the slaves.

29:05.711 --> 29:09.046
Would the overseer ever do
any kind of punishing,

29:09.048 --> 29:10.781
or was he just
in charge of --

29:10.783 --> 29:12.416
Yeah, he would do punishing,
as well.

29:12.418 --> 29:14.885
He would do it, as well.
Okay.

29:14.887 --> 29:17.755
Slaves would be whipped, beat.

29:17.757 --> 29:19.857
Some would be killed.

29:19.859 --> 29:21.058
Who's gonna stop them?

29:21.060 --> 29:22.626
- That's right.
- That's true.

29:22.628 --> 29:25.329
I mean, God.
Hmm.

29:25.331 --> 29:27.231
God, it's so hard
to fathom,

29:27.233 --> 29:29.166
but we can't
forget about it.

29:29.168 --> 29:31.835
Now, what's strange here
is that the overseer

29:31.837 --> 29:34.071
we've been kind
of delving into here

29:34.073 --> 29:36.106
just makes me wonder
what kind of person he was.

29:36.108 --> 29:37.407
And it's complete
speculation.

29:37.409 --> 29:38.575
We can't find any records
of him.

29:38.577 --> 29:40.410
He ended up
killing himself.

29:40.412 --> 29:42.112
- Oh, my goodness.
- And so...

29:42.114 --> 29:45.549
All the ones I know about
were just malicious people.

29:45.551 --> 29:47.184
Okay.

29:47.186 --> 29:49.086
BERRY: If Baldwin Lee is
in the caretaker's cottage,

29:49.088 --> 29:51.955
it would explain why we were met
with anger and aggression.

29:51.957 --> 29:54.358
His job was to control
and punish people,

29:54.360 --> 29:57.761
but it doesn't explain
why he's here.

29:57.763 --> 29:59.663
Now that we have a name,
we'll try and engage

29:59.665 --> 30:01.131
the foul-mouth entity to see

30:01.133 --> 30:02.966
if it's actually
the overseer Baldwin.

30:02.968 --> 30:07.237
♪♪

30:07.239 --> 30:08.572
BRUNI: All right.

30:08.574 --> 30:10.808
This little silver box
that I have in my hand --

30:10.810 --> 30:12.743
I know
it might seem strange,

30:12.745 --> 30:14.778
but this can
actually hear you.

30:14.780 --> 30:17.381
So go ahead and say
your name as loud

30:17.383 --> 30:20.284
as you can towards
this little red light.

30:20.286 --> 30:23.787
♪♪

30:23.789 --> 30:26.023
Nothing we've brought here
will hurt you.

30:26.025 --> 30:29.960
We are not here to cause
any harm to anybody.

30:29.962 --> 30:31.762
We're just here trying
to figure out

30:31.764 --> 30:35.465
who's hiding
in this building.

30:35.467 --> 30:38.702
Can you tell me
what family you work for?

30:38.704 --> 30:45.709
♪♪

30:45.711 --> 30:47.110
All right.

31:00.826 --> 31:01.825
[ <i> Indistinct voice</i> ]

31:01.827 --> 31:04.228
- What was that?
- I heard a name.

31:08.901 --> 31:10.567
Oh, my God!
That's his name!

31:10.569 --> 31:11.835
That's his name again.

31:18.878 --> 31:20.978
- Baldwin!
- Baldwin!

31:20.980 --> 31:24.348
♪♪

31:24.350 --> 31:27.551
BRUNI: <i> What happened to you</i>
<i> after the Civil War?</i>

31:27.553 --> 31:30.487
<i>...where you always lived</i>
<i> until the end?</i>

31:39.865 --> 31:44.334
♪♪

31:44.336 --> 31:46.270
BERRY: We are investigating
the caretaker's cottage,

31:46.272 --> 31:49.506
the place Michelle, the owner,
is terrified to enter.

31:49.508 --> 31:51.074
We need to figure out
if Baldwin Lee,

31:51.076 --> 31:53.877
the dead overseer, is here,
or if it's someone else.

31:53.879 --> 31:55.345
And we think we've just
got our answer.

31:56.649 --> 31:58.215
- Baldwin!
- Baldwin!

31:58.217 --> 32:00.117
BERRY: <i> We don't know</i>
<i> what your name is.</i>

32:00.119 --> 32:03.620
I mean, that's clear.

32:03.622 --> 32:06.490
BRUNI: <i> Can you tell me what</i>
<i> family you worked for?</i>

32:08.794 --> 32:10.127
- Turner.
- Oh, my God!

32:10.129 --> 32:11.228
Are you kidding me
right now?

32:11.230 --> 32:12.562
- Does that really say "Turner"?
- Yes!

32:12.564 --> 32:15.999
- I got to come over there.
- It says "Turner."

32:16.001 --> 32:17.734
Listen.

32:22.007 --> 32:23.507
Turner.

32:23.509 --> 32:26.176
Baldwin --
He's in this building.

32:28.347 --> 32:31.548
Now we have to get him
to talk to us more.

32:31.550 --> 32:32.983
All right.

32:32.985 --> 32:37.487
Baldwin, what happened to you
after the Civil War?

32:37.489 --> 32:44.161
♪♪

32:44.163 --> 32:48.065
Was this where you always
lived until the end?

32:50.035 --> 32:51.902
Did something bad
happen to you?

32:51.904 --> 32:58.475
♪♪

32:58.477 --> 33:00.544
Have you ever tried
to leave?

33:00.546 --> 33:04.648
♪♪

33:04.650 --> 33:06.917
Did someone stop you
from leaving?

33:06.919 --> 33:09.820
♪♪

33:09.822 --> 33:12.456
All right, let's see what
you had to say, Mr. Baldwin.

33:21.333 --> 33:24.267
Yes.

33:27.473 --> 33:29.172
BRUNI: <i> Have you ever</i>
<i> tried to leave?</i>

33:29.174 --> 33:30.574
- Oh, my God.
- There's something --

33:30.576 --> 33:32.142
Hold on.

33:37.516 --> 33:38.749
Suicide.

33:42.821 --> 33:44.021
Suicide.

33:44.023 --> 33:45.389
<i> Did someone stop you</i>
<i> from leaving?</i>

33:45.391 --> 33:49.793
♪♪

33:49.795 --> 33:51.261
I mean,
from what we know,

33:51.263 --> 33:52.896
we know
the Turners were here.

33:52.898 --> 33:54.064
Mm-hmm.

33:54.066 --> 33:55.699
The fact that we know
the research, I mean,

33:55.701 --> 33:59.403
it's saying it to us
in our face right now --

33:59.405 --> 34:00.704
is incredible.

34:00.706 --> 34:02.706
He said his name.
He said, "Turner."

34:02.708 --> 34:04.007
He said, "Suicide."

34:04.009 --> 34:06.676
We know those three things.
He's here.

34:06.678 --> 34:07.944
It's insane.

34:07.946 --> 34:10.679
What's also crazy, and
I hate talking about it

34:10.681 --> 34:12.516
because I know
that he's listening --

34:12.518 --> 34:14.618
Can we talk about this
outside for a minute?

34:14.620 --> 34:16.319
I'm serious.
- Yeah.

34:16.321 --> 34:17.821
- I don't want to talk in here.
- Yeah, I do, too.

34:17.822 --> 34:23.460
♪♪

34:23.462 --> 34:27.630
What's happened here
is we've established trust

34:27.632 --> 34:30.634
with someone who probably
isn't a very good guy.

34:30.636 --> 34:33.804
- No.
- What he did was unthinkable.

34:33.806 --> 34:36.505
But at the same time,

34:36.507 --> 34:39.242
we have to carry on this
conversation.

34:39.244 --> 34:40.377
Well, right.
Right.

34:40.379 --> 34:41.978
Like, there's a moral
dilemma here.

34:41.980 --> 34:44.414
Do we speak
to him on the truth

34:44.416 --> 34:45.715
and risk him shutting down

34:45.717 --> 34:47.583
and not speaking to us again
and not getting anywhere?

34:47.585 --> 34:49.386
Exactly.
And he did it to himself.

34:49.388 --> 34:50.954
Did he do it out of guilt?
- We don't know that yet.

34:50.956 --> 34:53.123
Do we know
what his motivation is?

34:53.125 --> 34:56.293
- I mean...
- It's so tough.

34:56.295 --> 34:58.462
We have to keep him
talking to us...

34:58.464 --> 34:59.830
Mm-hmm.

34:59.832 --> 35:01.398
...so that he will tell us
this information,

35:01.400 --> 35:04.968
rather than shutting him off
and alienating him.

35:04.970 --> 35:06.269
Yeah,
let's just try to --

35:06.271 --> 35:08.205
Try to go and, like,
just do this.

35:08.207 --> 35:09.673
Yeah.

35:09.675 --> 35:12.576
BRUNI: We are talking to a guy
who beat people for a living.

35:12.578 --> 35:15.278
It is going to be tough
being polite to him.

35:15.280 --> 35:16.813
But we have a job to do.

35:16.815 --> 35:19.349
We need to figure out why
Baldwin Lee is here,

35:19.351 --> 35:21.952
and in the process of getting
answers from Michelle,

35:21.954 --> 35:25.188
maybe we can figure out
why he won't leave.

35:25.190 --> 35:27.491
Baldwin, thank you
for talking to us.

35:27.493 --> 35:30.861
Is there a reason why you
were so forthcoming

35:30.863 --> 35:32.696
with that information?

35:32.698 --> 35:37.367
♪♪

35:37.369 --> 35:39.135
Are you regretful?

35:39.137 --> 35:43.240
♪♪

35:43.242 --> 35:47.077
Can you help us understand
the work that you did here?

35:47.079 --> 35:49.846
♪♪

35:49.848 --> 35:51.815
We want
to understand you.

36:04.796 --> 36:07.030
He says, "Regretful."

36:07.032 --> 36:09.900
♪♪

36:09.902 --> 36:11.901
We would love for you
to go out to that house

36:11.903 --> 36:15.205
and just have a little
conversation with Mr. Lee.

36:15.207 --> 36:17.440
This has to be something
between he and I by ourselves.

36:25.617 --> 36:29.553
♪♪

36:29.555 --> 36:31.354
BRUNI: We are in
the caretaker's cottage.

36:31.356 --> 36:33.790
We've just discovered that
the menacing ghost

36:33.792 --> 36:35.992
torturing Michelle
and her guests

36:35.994 --> 36:39.329
is an angry overseer
by the name of Baldwin Lee.

36:39.331 --> 36:41.531
He took his own life in 1868,

36:41.533 --> 36:43.667
but we still don't know
why he is here.

36:55.781 --> 36:56.947
Yeah.

36:56.949 --> 37:00.083
BRUNI: <i> Is there a reason</i>
<i> that you...</i>

37:00.085 --> 37:02.252
I've got
the shivers all over.

37:02.254 --> 37:05.222
BERRY:
<i> Can you help us understand</i>

37:05.224 --> 37:07.457
<i> the work that you do here?</i>

37:07.459 --> 37:08.892
I think he might
be done talking.

37:11.496 --> 37:15.398
It's hard to be that nice
to someone.

37:15.400 --> 37:16.600
Yeah.

37:16.602 --> 37:19.336
Mr. Lee, we're gonna go
and give you some space.

37:19.338 --> 37:26.543
♪♪

37:26.545 --> 37:28.979
Um...

37:28.981 --> 37:31.114
Okay, so, I think...
- Yeah.

37:31.116 --> 37:32.315
...he thinks it's bad.

37:32.317 --> 37:33.717
Mm-hmm.

37:33.719 --> 37:34.818
Whatever was bad to him
that he did to himself,

37:34.820 --> 37:36.786
he --
that, to me, is regret.

37:36.788 --> 37:38.121
Yeah.

37:38.123 --> 37:39.956
And you know sometimes
when we meet people like this

37:39.958 --> 37:43.193
that have done these things,
they -- they can change.

37:43.195 --> 37:44.694
- Right.
- Like, their thing --

37:44.696 --> 37:48.898
their being in the afterlife
sort of changes who they are.

37:48.900 --> 37:50.267
Right.

37:50.269 --> 37:51.835
BERRY: We have shocking
information to tell Michelle,

37:51.837 --> 37:55.071
and we're not sure
how she's going to handle it.

37:55.073 --> 37:56.072
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

37:56.074 --> 37:58.074
- How's it going?
- Good.

37:58.076 --> 38:00.277
BRUNI:
Welcome back to your home.

38:00.279 --> 38:01.911
Thank you.

38:01.913 --> 38:04.414
Well, so, first of all,
I just wanted to say

38:04.416 --> 38:06.516
that we really enjoyed
spending a few days here

38:06.518 --> 38:09.386
because it's a very
comfortable place.

38:09.388 --> 38:10.854
Like, we never, at any point,

38:10.856 --> 38:15.492
felt threatened
or uncomfortable.

38:15.494 --> 38:17.727
I think that it's safe to say
for your guests

38:17.729 --> 38:20.864
and everything that the place
is a wonderful environment.

38:20.866 --> 38:23.366
It's beautiful.
- Thank you.

38:23.368 --> 38:25.035
So, what we really focused on
was we really wanted

38:25.037 --> 38:28.638
to find out what was going on
in the cottage

38:28.640 --> 38:31.541
just because that seemed
to be the area

38:31.543 --> 38:33.643
where you were
the most concerned.

38:33.645 --> 38:38.315
Right away, he was pretty direct
about having us in there

38:38.317 --> 38:40.050
and how he felt about it.

38:45.891 --> 38:47.257
Saying, "'F' you."

38:47.259 --> 38:48.191
- Yes.
- You did hear that.

38:48.193 --> 38:49.893
- Okay, twice.
- Okay.

38:49.895 --> 38:51.127
- Twice in a row.
- Twice in a row.

38:51.129 --> 38:53.196
Within seconds of us
trying to talk to him.

38:53.198 --> 38:56.399
So, the first thing this guy
is saying to us is intense.

38:56.401 --> 38:58.335
He doesn't want anything
to do with us.

38:58.337 --> 39:00.203
We're just like, "Okay,
let's figure this out."

39:00.205 --> 39:01.971
So, we kind of came back at him.

39:01.973 --> 39:03.073
These are the responses.

39:10.449 --> 39:11.715
Did you hear "Baldwin"?

39:11.717 --> 39:13.016
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah.

39:13.018 --> 39:14.718
So, what do you know
about Baldwin?

39:14.720 --> 39:16.419
- "Baldwin" was Baldwin Lee.
- Mm-hmm.

39:16.421 --> 39:19.155
He was one of the last overseers
at Belle Grove.

39:19.157 --> 39:21.224
We asked him at one point,
you know,

39:21.226 --> 39:23.126
"What happened to you?"
- "Did something bad happen?"

39:23.128 --> 39:24.494
"Did something bad happen
to you?"

39:24.496 --> 39:25.762
And he answers.

39:30.335 --> 39:31.668
<i> Have you ever tried to leave?</i>
Suicide.

39:31.670 --> 39:32.902
Yeah.

39:32.904 --> 39:34.437
He committed suicide
by slitting his own throat

39:34.439 --> 39:35.972
with a straight razor.
- Ooh!

39:35.974 --> 39:37.407
Yeah, it's more graphic

39:37.409 --> 39:39.476
than you could
possibly imagine.

39:39.478 --> 39:41.311
And so we feel like
what happened

39:41.313 --> 39:45.248
is he's such
a conflicted character

39:45.250 --> 39:48.651
because he's someone
that we hate what he did,

39:48.653 --> 39:51.254
and we're not justifying
any of it.

39:51.256 --> 39:53.056
He seems very conflicted.

39:53.058 --> 39:54.924
But what we think happened --

39:54.926 --> 39:57.193
where he's come back here
is like --

39:57.195 --> 39:58.762
almost like a self-imposed
sentence.

39:58.764 --> 40:00.497
Like, we find this sometimes.

40:00.499 --> 40:04.100
For him, we suspect
he's very regretful

40:04.102 --> 40:06.136
and that he is not
going to leave

40:06.138 --> 40:08.905
because he doesn't feel like
he deserves to move on.

40:08.907 --> 40:11.441
So, that being said,
what we would love

40:11.443 --> 40:14.244
for you to do,
and we will go with you --

40:14.246 --> 40:16.312
is we would love for you
to go out to the house

40:16.314 --> 40:19.115
and just have a little
conversation with Mr. Lee.

40:19.117 --> 40:20.583
How do you feel about it?

40:20.585 --> 40:21.985
- Nervous.
- I know.

40:21.987 --> 40:25.121
We just know
if you talk to him,

40:25.123 --> 40:28.758
you actually might start feeling
more comfortable in that space,

40:28.760 --> 40:30.593
enough to do something with it.

40:30.595 --> 40:33.763
It's just -- It's like you guys
have to kind of work together.

40:33.765 --> 40:36.199
- I could try.
- Okay, let's try it.

40:38.003 --> 40:40.370
BERRY: Plantations are
inherently violent places

40:40.372 --> 40:43.139
and stand for a time
we can't forget.

40:43.141 --> 40:45.842
- Are you ready?
- I think so.

40:45.844 --> 40:47.210
All right, let's do this.

40:47.212 --> 40:49.345
BERRY: But Belle Grove
is not a dark place now.

40:49.347 --> 40:51.714
And even though we don't agree
with who Baldwin was

40:51.716 --> 40:54.551
and what he did,
we can't change history.

40:54.553 --> 40:55.819
But we can help the living.

40:55.821 --> 40:57.554
BRUNI:
All right, deep breath.

41:01.059 --> 41:02.258
Here we go.

41:02.260 --> 41:03.593
Good?

41:03.595 --> 41:05.295
Come on in
between us.

41:05.297 --> 41:06.930
That way...

41:06.932 --> 41:09.399
Just be careful.

41:09.401 --> 41:11.267
Mr. Lee.

41:11.269 --> 41:14.537
Amy and Adam
are back with Michelle.

41:14.539 --> 41:17.674
Baldwin, this is Michelle.

41:17.676 --> 41:19.008
You're okay.
You got this.

41:19.010 --> 41:22.979
♪♪

41:22.981 --> 41:24.614
No.
- No?

41:24.616 --> 41:25.949
- No.
- Okay.

41:25.951 --> 41:27.750
- I'm sorry.
- No, no, you're good.

41:27.752 --> 41:31.254
- It's okay. It's all right.
- You're good.

41:31.256 --> 41:32.922
BERRY:
It's one step at a time.

41:32.924 --> 41:40.363
♪♪

41:40.365 --> 41:41.998
- I know.
- What are you feeling?

41:42.000 --> 41:44.501
This has to be something
between he and I by ourselves.

41:44.503 --> 41:46.603
- Yeah.
- Okay.

41:46.605 --> 41:51.741
Sometimes it's not a matter
of just an overnight resolution.

41:51.743 --> 41:53.176
Mm-hmm.

41:53.178 --> 41:54.711
And that I feel like
is what's happening here.

41:54.713 --> 41:57.013
- Yeah.
- It'll happen. Just not now.

41:57.015 --> 41:58.114
- It's okay.
- It's okay.

41:58.116 --> 41:59.549
- You're good.
- You didn't --

41:59.551 --> 42:01.284
You're standing on the porch,
and you went inside.

42:01.286 --> 42:03.152
We're proud of you.

42:03.154 --> 42:06.723
BRUNI: This particular case was
so much harder than most for us.

42:06.725 --> 42:08.725
It's not always easy separating

42:08.727 --> 42:11.828
our personal feelings
from the evidence.

42:11.830 --> 42:13.496
BERRY: Honestly, that was
a great first step.

42:13.498 --> 42:15.999
The relationship between
Michelle and Baldwin

42:16.001 --> 42:18.101
has always been based on fear,

42:18.103 --> 42:20.904
but maybe Baldwin is somehow
trying to atone

42:20.906 --> 42:23.606
for the sins
he committed in his life.

42:23.608 --> 42:26.042
Our hope is one day
this will allow Michelle

42:26.044 --> 42:29.546
to stand up to him and feel safe
in the caretaker's cottage.

